            <thetext>Created attachment 900
a small demo about this stuff...just drag and drop an image from your desktop

The HTML5 Drag and Drop API togheter with the File API allows us to do that. Drag and Drop gives us a nice way to get the files while File API, trough a FileReader obj let&#39;s us read them.


Unfortunately, the File API Browser Support is kind of slim for now (http://caniuse.com/#search=File API) so let&#39;s just wait and see what happens because this is such a nice feature to have.

For more check out this html5rocks tutorial. At the end, you will find some more resources.
http://www.html5rocks.com/tutorials/dnd/basics/
http://www.html5rocks.com/tutorials/file/dndfiles/</thetext>
